The author of the article emphasizes that healthcare is a right, not a privilege, and that all Americans should have access to quality and affordable healthcare. They express the importance of this, particularly in the midst of the COVID-19 pandemic, which has had devastating consequences on people's health and claimed the lives of many. The author announces that HealthCare.gov will be open for all Americans to sign up for health insurance from today until May 15, 2021. They also highlight the efforts of Congress to pass the American Rescue Plan, which aims to increase testing, tracing, and vaccination efforts, as well as lower health costs and expand access to care. The plan includes increasing federal subsidies and decreasing premiums, ensuring that no one pays more than 8.5 percent of their income for health coverage. It also incentivizes states to expand coverage and provides opportunities for extending coverage for low-income women who have recently given birth. The author encourages everyone who needs health insurance to visit HealthCare.gov and assist others in signing up. They believe that by working together to expand coverage, lower costs, and ensure healthcare as a right, the country can overcome the crisis.